import CsdLean4.Mathlib.Analysis.InnerProductSpace.KahlerForm
import CsdLean4.Mathlib.LinearAlgebra.Projectivization.TransitionProbability
import CsdLean4.LF4.ProjectedDynamics

/-!
# The Schr√∂dinger flow is a K√§hler symplectomorphism

**Category:** 3-Local (The Schr√∂dinger flow is a K√§hler symplectomorphism).

This ties the pointwise K√§hler form (`Mathlib/Analysis/InnerProductSpace/KahlerForm.lean`) to the
Schr√∂dinger pillar (`schrodingerUnitary`, `LF4/ProjectedDynamics.lean`): the deterministic quantum
evolution `exp(-itH)` **preserves the Fubini‚ÄďStudy K√§hler structure** ‚ÄĒ the metric `g = re‚ü™¬∑,¬∑‚üę` and
the fundamental form `ŌČ = im‚ü™¬∑,¬∑‚üę`. So Schr√∂dinger evolution is a *symplectic isometry* (a
symplectomorphism) of the projective phase space ‚ÄĒ the Kibble / Ashtekar‚ÄďSchilling picture of quantum
mechanics as classical Hamiltonian mechanics on the K√§hler manifold `‚Ąā‚Ąô^{N-1}`, at the
pointwise/linear level.

The mechanism is elementary: `exp(-itH)` is unitary (`schrodingerUnitary`,
`expNegITH_unitary_group`), so it preserves the Hermitian inner product
(`inner_toEuclideanLin_unitary`), hence its real and imaginary parts `g` and `ŌČ`.

## Why this matters (and its honest scope)

This is the first rung of the geometric-QM statement "Schr√∂dinger evolution is Hamiltonian flow on the
Fubini‚ÄďStudy phase space" ‚ÄĒ the *dynamics-preserves-the-form* half. It connects, in one theorem, the
K√§hler form, the Schr√∂dinger flow, and the geometric (Kibble/Ashtekar‚ÄďSchilling) formulation. It is the
form-level companion to the geometric phase / action (Aharonov‚ÄďAnandan), whose primitive is the
symplectic potential of `ŌČ`.

It does **NOT** derive the flow FROM the form (the Hamiltonian-vector-field statement `X_H = ŌČ‚ĀĽ¬ĻdH`,
`KG-2`) ‚ÄĒ that needs the symplectic-gradient / manifold-differential API Mathlib lacks and stays
blocked. This module proves the invariance (a symmetry of `ŌČ`), not the generation. It is at the
Hilbert-vector level; the descent to the ray-level FS form rides on the tangent-space `J`-invariance
(`Kahler.tangent_complexStructure_invariant`).
-/

open Kahler MeasureTheory Projectivization

namespace CSD.LF4

variable {N : ‚Ąē}

/-- **The Schr√∂dinger flow on the state vector.** `exp(-itH)` acting on `Ōą ‚ąą ‚Ąā^N`, i.e. the
deterministic unitary evolution `schrodingerUnitary hH t` applied as a linear map. -/
noncomputable def schrodingerVectorFlow {H : Matrix (Fin N) (Fin N) ‚Ąā} (hH : H.IsHermitian)
    (t : ‚ĄĚ) (v : EuclideanSpace ‚Ąā (Fin N)) : EuclideanSpace ‚Ąā (Fin N) :=
  Matrix.toEuclideanLin (schrodingerUnitary hH t).val v

/-- **Schr√∂dinger evolution preserves the metric `g`.** `g (U_t u) (U_t v) = g u v` for
`U_t = exp(-itH)` ‚ÄĒ the flow is a `g`-isometry (it preserves the Fubini‚ÄďStudy Riemannian metric). -/
theorem schrodingerVectorFlow_preserves_metric {H : Matrix (Fin N) (Fin N) ‚Ąā} (hH : H.IsHermitian)
    (t : ‚ĄĚ) (u v : EuclideanSpace ‚Ąā (Fin N)) :
    metric (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t u) (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t v) = metric u v := by
  simp only [metric, schrodingerVectorFlow, inner_toEuclideanLin_unitary]

/-- **Schr√∂dinger evolution preserves the fundamental form `ŌČ`.** `ŌČ (U_t u) (U_t v) = ŌČ u v` for
`U_t = exp(-itH)` ‚ÄĒ the flow is a symplectomorphism (it preserves the Fubini‚ÄďStudy symplectic form). -/
theorem schrodingerVectorFlow_preserves_fundamentalForm {H : Matrix (Fin N) (Fin N) ‚Ąā}
    (hH : H.IsHermitian) (t : ‚ĄĚ) (u v : EuclideanSpace ‚Ąā (Fin N)) :
    fundamentalForm (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t u) (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t v)
      = fundamentalForm u v := by
  simp only [fundamentalForm, schrodingerVectorFlow, inner_toEuclideanLin_unitary]

/-- **Schr√∂dinger evolution is a K√§hler symplectomorphism.** The deterministic flow `exp(-itH)`
preserves BOTH the Fubini‚ÄďStudy metric `g` and the symplectic form `ŌČ`:
`g (U_t u)(U_t v) = g u v` and `ŌČ (U_t u)(U_t v) = ŌČ u v`. So quantum evolution is a symplectic isometry
of the K√§hler geometry of `‚Ąā‚Ąô^{N-1}` ‚ÄĒ the Kibble / Ashtekar‚ÄďSchilling geometric picture (QM as
Hamiltonian mechanics on the Fubini‚ÄďStudy phase space), at the pointwise/linear level. Ties the K√§hler
form to the Schr√∂dinger pillar; the converse (flow generated BY the form, `X_H = ŌČ‚ĀĽ¬ĻdH`, KG-2) needs
the manifold symplectic-gradient API Mathlib lacks and stays blocked. -/
theorem schrodinger_flow_kahler_symplectomorphism {H : Matrix (Fin N) (Fin N) ‚Ąā}
    (hH : H.IsHermitian) (t : ‚ĄĚ) (u v : EuclideanSpace ‚Ąā (Fin N)) :
    metric (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t u) (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t v) = metric u v
    ‚ąß fundamentalForm (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t u) (schrodingerVectorFlow hH t v)
        = fundamentalForm u v :=
  ‚ü®schrodingerVectorFlow_preserves_metric hH t u v,
    schrodingerVectorFlow_preserves_fundamentalForm hH t u v‚ü©

end CSD.LF4


